==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*tungōn'', from Indo-European ''{{Unicode|*dn̥ĝʰū-}}''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[tunge]], Old Saxon [[tunga]]  (Dutch [[tong]]), Old Franconian [[tunga]], Old High German [[zunge]] (German [[Zunge]]), Old Norse [[tunga]] (Swedish [[tunga]]), Gothic {{Unicode|[[𐍄𐌿𐌲𐌲𐍉]]}}.

''Indo-European cognates:'' Sanskrit {{Unicode|[[जिह्वा]]}}, Archaic Latin [[dingua]] (Latin [[lingua]], French [[langue]]), Avestan ''hizvā'', Old Church Slavonic [[ѩзыкъ]] (Russian [[язык]]), Lithuanian [[liežuvis|liežùvis]], Old Irish [[tenge]] (Welsh [[tafod]]), Tocharian A ''käntu''.

